Interface Expectations.Unless

  • Enclosing class:
    Expectations
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface Expectations.Unless

    An interface used as a return value of Expectations.fail(Function) method.

    • Method Detail

      • unless

        <T> T unless(Statement<T> statement)

        Validates a given statement and if it is valid, the target value of it will be returned. Otherwise, an exception should be thrown.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the target value of statement.
        Parameters:
        statement - A statement to be validated.
        Returns:
        A target value of statement, if the statement is evaluated true.

      • unless

        default void unless(Statement<?>... statements)

        This doesn’t return any value because it cannot be determined which value should be the one to be returned.

        Parameters:
        statements - Statements to be validated.
